
========
Overview
========

rulengd listens for events and executes speficied methods if the incoming event
arguments contain speficied ones. Events and methods are specified in UCI config
file, e.g.

config rule
    option event 'wifi.radio.channel_changed'
    list event_data "{'reason': 1}" 
    list event_data "{'channels': [1, 2, 3]}"
    option method 'file->write'
    list method_data "{'path': '/tmp/test_file.txt'}"
    list method_data "{'data': 'channel changed!'}"

This means we are listening for 'wifi.radio.channel_changed' event. If that
event occurs, and contains arguments {'reason': 1} and {'channels': [1, 2, 3]},
we execute method 'write' on object 'file' with arguments {'path':
'/tmp/test_file.txt'} and {'data': 'channel changed!'}. Object and array
arguments must be primitive types (we can't have object in the array).

========
Building
========

mkdir build && cd build
cmake ..
make

========
Example
========

After building, do 'sudo make install'. This will copy
'./test/ruleng-test-rules' to '/etc/config'. Start 'rulengd', and test it with

ubus send "wifi.radio.channel_changed" "{'radio':0, 'reason':1, 'channels': [1,2,3], 'non-specified-key': 'non-specified-value'}".

This should write 'channel changed!' in the '/tmp/test_file.txt'.
